item.dc:creator: @zoltanman zoltanman
item.description:
@zoltanman wrote:

[quote=“recker450, post:2, topic:358360”]replace your addactionbutton

[quote] public static void addActionButton(int i, int j, int k, int width, int height, String s)
{
Class9 class9 = aClass9Array210[i] = new Class9();
class9.anInt250 = i;
class9.anInt236 = i;
class9.anInt262 = 5;
class9.anInt217 = 1;
class9.anInt214 = 0;
class9.anInt220 = width;
class9.anInt267 = height;
class9.aByte254 = 0;
class9.anInt230 = 52;
class9.aClass30_Sub2_Sub1_Sub1_207 = SpriteLoader(j, “Custom”);
class9.aClass30_Sub2_Sub1_Sub1_260 = SpriteLoader(k, “Custom”);
class9.aString221 = s;
}[/quote][/quote]

Yes.

The parameters of the method didn’t match the method you were trying to call.

ex:

void methodOne(int num, int num2) {
    myAge = num;
    myBirthYear = num2;
}

Wrong:

methodOne(19, 1991, 1);

Right:

methodOne(19, 1991);
